enhanced_by.reason: The pop method relies on the stack having elements, which can be ensured by pushing elements onto the stack.
Checking if the stack is empty before calling pop can help in handling the EmptyStackException.
Both pop and peek methods interact with the top element of the stack, making peek a good candidate for assertions related to the state of the stack after pop.
The search method can be used to verify the absence of the popped element from the stack after the pop operation.
